SIMPLE: acetabulum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acetabulum
<hw>Ac`e*tab"u*lum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
little saucer for vinegar, fr. <ets>acetum</ets> vinegar, fr.
<ets>acere</ets> to be sour.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A vinegar cup; socket of
the hip bone; a measure of about one eighth of a pint, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The bony cup which
receives the head of the thigh bone.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The cavity
in which the leg of an insect is inserted at its articulation with the
body.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A sucker of the sepia or cuttlefish and
related animals.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>The large posterior sucker of
the leeches.</def> <sd>(e)</sd> <def>One of the lobes of the placenta in
ruminating animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acetal</ent>⟦br⟧
